<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,721,962]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,757,782]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Comments.</emphasis>
As shown in 
<bibRefCitation author="Mah, C. L." box="[491,627,757,782]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="917 - 954" refId="ref72068" refString="Mah, C. L. (2006) Phylogeny and biogeography of the deep-sea goniasterid, Circeaster (Echinodermata: Asteroidea) including descriptions of six new species. Zoosystema, 28 (4), 917 - 954." type="journal article" year="2006">Mah (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1909" box="[639,744,757,782]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Lydiaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[639,744,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Lydiaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<emphasis box="[978,1098,758,781]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1909" box="[978,1095,758,781]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Circeaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Circeaster</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
differing primarily in that the abactinal disk plates do not abruptly enlarge on the arm as they do on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1909" box="[982,1098,794,817]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Circeaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[982,1098,794,817]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Circeaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Other species of 
<emphasis box="[1315,1436,794,817]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1909" box="[1315,1432,794,817]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Circeaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Circeaster</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
including the widely occurring 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mah" authorityYear="2006" box="[501,718,829,854]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Circeaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="arandae">
<emphasis box="[501,718,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Circeaster arandae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[786,921,829,854]" name="Madagascar" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mah" authorityYear="2006" box="[975,1168,829,854]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Circeaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="pullus">
<emphasis box="[975,1168,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Circeaster pullus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mah" authorityYear="2006" box="[1222,1436,829,854]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Circeaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="sandrae">
<emphasis box="[1222,1436,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Circeaster sandrae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the central and South Pacific Ocean have been observed 
<taxonomicName box="[893,966,865,890]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Iconaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="58" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="situ">in situ</taxonomicName>
and appear to be predators of deep-sea octocorals (
<bibRefCitation author="Mah, C. L." box="[284,406,901,926]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="917 - 954" refId="ref72068" refString="Mah, C. L. (2006) Phylogeny and biogeography of the deep-sea goniasterid, Circeaster (Echinodermata: Asteroidea) including descriptions of six new species. Zoosystema, 28 (4), 917 - 954." type="journal article" year="2006">Mah 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mah, C. L." box="[420,479,901,926]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="211 - 228" refId="ref72184" refString="Mah, C. L. (2015) New species, corallivory, in situ video observations and overview of the Goniasteridae (Valvatida, Asteroidea) in the Hawaiian Region. Zootaxa, 3926 (2), 211 - 228. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3926.2.3" type="journal article" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
; Mah unpublished data from R/V Okeanos Explorer). 
<taxonomicName authority="Mah, 2018" authorityName="Mah" authorityYear="2018" box="[1113,1221,901,926]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Wallastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[1113,1221,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Wallastra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1231,1310,902,926]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(described below) also shows some character similarity with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1909" box="[711,828,938,961]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Circeaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[711,828,938,961]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Circeaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1909" box="[883,986,937,962]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Lydiaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[883,986,937,962]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Lydiaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
